gw.datatype

Enum JdbcType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<JdbcType>
      • gw.datatype.JdbcType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<JdbcType>

    public enum JdbcType
extends java.lang.Enum<JdbcType>
    Represents JDBC types supported by Guidewire.

    Each type is represented in Java according to the following table:

    JDBC typeJava Class
    BITBoolean
    BLOBBlob
    BOOLEANBoolean
    CLOBString
    DECIMALBigDecimal
    DOUBLEDouble
    FLOATFloat
    INTEGERInteger
    TIMESTAMPTimestamp
    VARCHARString
    VARBINARYbyte[]
    SPATIAL_POINTSpatialPoint
    SPATIAL_POLYGONSpatialPolygon

    For the most part, this table reflects the standard JDBC type -> class mappings, with the following exceptions:

    • BLOB is represented with a Blob instead of a Blob.
    • CLOB is represented with a String instead of a Clob.
